{"id":18566,"date":"2014-03-17T11:19:46","date_gmt":"2014-03-17T07:19:46","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=18566"},"modified":"2024-02-22T10:35:51","modified_gmt":"2024-02-22T06:35:51","slug":"zakat-food-clothing-charity","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/17\/zakat-food-clothing-charity\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Zakat: If he gives food, clothing, or prayer in charity"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>When a man earns wealth from what is lawful and he feeds himself, or clothes another among the creation of Allah, it will be regarded as charity <\/b><b>for him. When a Muslim man is without means to give in charity, he should say: O Allah, send blessings upon Muhammad, Your servant and Messenger, and send blessings upon the believing men and women and the Muslim men and women. If he says this, it will be regarded as charity for him<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 1176<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/i>(authentic) according to Al-Suyuti<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064d \u0643\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0628\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0627 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u062d\u064e\u0644\u0627\u0644\u064d \u0641\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0637\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0646\u064e